+{
+  "body": "During hive-mind PR https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1044 for issue https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1043, I reviewed the latest JavaScript package `agent-commander@0.4.3` against hive-mind's embedded tool adapters.\n\nThe current hive-mind integration can route basic execution through `agent-commander`, but several hive-mind options still cannot be expressed through the public agent-commander API without falling back to direct tool-specific command construction.\n\nNeeded parity surface:\n\n- Claude: thinking budget / effort env handling, 1M context disable behavior, sub-session auto-compact envs, MCP config without Playwright, useless/disallowed tool flags, read-only / permission modes, verbose/fallback/resume/session behavior, and custom binary/env passthrough.\n- Codex: reasoning effort mapping, context window / auto-compact config, MCP config generation, sandbox/approval mode parity, custom binary/env passthrough, and the prompt-file path used for large prompts.\n- OpenCode: config/permission env parity, custom binary/env passthrough, and prompt-file or equivalent large-prompt support.\n- `agent`: hive-mind verbose handling, resume/no-fork equivalents where supported, permission/config parity, custom binary/env passthrough, and full JSON usage/result reporting.\n\nRequest:\n\nProvide typed agent-commander options or a documented raw args/env/config passthrough that lets hive-mind control these features only through agent-commander when `--use-agent-commander` is enabled. This would let hive-mind remove remaining adapter-level compromises while keeping default embedded execution unchanged.",
+  "createdAt": "2026-05-01T05:12:29Z",
+  "number": 29,
+  "state": "OPEN",
+  "title": "Expose hive-mind execution parity options for claude/codex/opencode/agent",
+  "url": "https://github.com/link-assistant/agent-commander/issues/29"
+}
